
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `fprintd-enroll` baraye sabt angosht baraye estefade az fingerprint scanner (angosht n نگار خوان) dar Linux estefade mishavad. In dastoor be shoma komak mikonad ke angosht khod ra baraye vorood be system ya anjam karhaye amniati sabt konid.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `fprintd-enroll` -->  👣 Angosht ra sabt mikonad.  Shoma bayad etela'at lazem ra be dastoor bedahid.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ fprintd-enroll username

    🔹 Angosht ra baraye karbar ba username 'username' sabt mikonad. Az shoma khaste mishavad ke angosht khod ra chand bar baraye scanner bezarid.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ fprintd-enroll ali

    🔹 Angosht ali ra sabt mikonad.  Dar hale sabt, system az ali mikahad ke angosht khod ra chand bar baraye scanner bezarad ta اطمینان حاصل شود ke tasvir dorost ast.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `fprintd-enroll` command is used to enroll your fingerprint for use with fingerprint scanners in Linux. This command helps you register your fingerprint for system login or other security-related tasks.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `fprintd-enroll` --> 👣 Enrolls a fingerprint. You need to provide the necessary information to the command.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ fprintd-enroll username

    🔹 Enrolls a fingerprint for the user with the username 'username'. You will be prompted to scan your finger multiple times.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ fprintd-enroll ali

    🔹 Enrolls Ali's fingerprint. During enrollment, the system will prompt Ali to place their finger on the scanner several times to ensure a good image is captured.
